Package model

Class Event

java.lang.Object
model.Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Event
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
Event represents an event that can be booked by Consumers. Tickets can be free, but they are required to attend, and there is a maximum cap on the number of tickets that can be booked.

      public Event​(long eventNumber, java.lang.String title, EventType type, int numTicketsCap, int ticketPriceInPence, java.lang.String venueAddress, java.lang.String description, java.time.LocalDateTime startDateTime, java.time.LocalDateTime endDateTime, EventTagCollection tags)
      Create a new Event with status = EventStatus.ACTIVE
      Parameters:
      eventNumber - unique event identifier
      title - name of the event
      type - type of the event
      numTicketsCap - maximum number of tickets, initially all available for booking
      ticketPriceInPence - price of each ticket in GBP pence
      venueAddress - address where the performance will be taking place
      description - additional details about the event, e.g., who the performers in a concert will be or if payment is required on entry in addition to ticket booking
      startDateTime - date and time when the performance will begin
      endDateTime - date and time when the performance will end
      tags - the event tags
